            "body": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/24338 would definitely resolve this.\n\nAlthough in my particular case, I have a proprietary LSP server that has non-standard completion-like features, and I want to hook that into Nvim completion / autocompletion plugins without having modify the LSP server. (I'm guessing I could also redefine some `vim.lsp.Client` handlers to hack this, haven't tried yet.)",
